com.att.research.xacml.std.dom

Class DOMResponse

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.att.research.xacml.std.dom.DOMResponse

  • public class DOMResponse
extends java.lang.Object
    DOMResponse is used to convert XML into Response objects and Response objects into XML strings. Instances of this class are never created. The Response objects returned by this class are instances of StdMutableResponse. Response objects are generated by loading a file or XML Node tree representing the Request. In normal product operation this is not used to generate new instances because the PDP generates StdResponse objects internally. Those objects are converted to XML strings for transmission through the RESTful Web Service using the convert method in this class.
    Version:
    $Revision: 1.2 $
    Author:
    car
